) he giveth this note of the truth of it.ſitales ſierine n • in nullo diſſentium a mandatus. Hom. 26. in Numb. If they be ſuch as diſſent not from the Commandements, nor do not croſſe by their courſes the Evangelical Precepts, then are they farre from contention. But on the other ſide, they who walk contrary to God & obey not his Goſpel, and follow the councels of their owne hearts, are by this Rule convinced to be the men of contention, and therefore men of Faction.
